verses.text: O give thanks unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, for \add he is\add* good : for his mercy \add endureth\add* for ever. \q1
Let the redeemed of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* say \add so\add*, whom he hath redeemed from the hand of the enemy ; \q1
And gathered them out of the lands , from the east , and from the west , from the north , and from the south.\f + \fr 107.3 \ft south: Heb. sea\f* \q1
They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way ; they found no city to dwell in. \q1
Hungry and thirsty , their soul fainted in them. \q1
Then they cried unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in their trouble , \add and\add* he delivered them out of their distresses. \q1
And he led them forth by the right way , that they might go to a city of habitation. \q1
Oh that \add men\add* would praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add for\add* his goodness , and \add for\add* his wonderful works to the children of men ! \q1
For he satisfieth the longing soul , and filleth the hungry soul with goodness. \b \q1
Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death , \add being\add* bound in affliction and iron ; \q1
Because they rebelled against the words of God , and contemned the counsel of the most High : \q1
Therefore he brought down their heart with labour ; they fell down , and \add there was\add* none to help. \q1
Then they cried unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in their trouble , \add and\add* he saved them out of their distresses. \q1
He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death , and brake their bands in sunder. \q1
Oh that \add men\add* would praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add for\add* his goodness , and \add for\add* his wonderful works to the children of men ! \q1
For he hath broken the gates of brass , and cut the bars of iron in sunder. \b \q1
Fools because of their transgression , and because of their iniquities , are afflicted. \q1
Their soul abhorreth all manner of meat ; and they draw near unto the gates of death. \q1
Then they cry unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in their trouble , \add and\add* he saveth them out of their distresses. \q1
He sent his word , and healed them, and delivered \add them\add* from their destructions. \q1
Oh that \add men\add* would praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add for\add* his goodness , and \add for\add* his wonderful works to the children of men ! \q1
And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving , and declare his works with rejoicing.\f + \fr 107.22 \ft rejoicing: Heb. singing\f* \b \q1
They that go down to the sea in ships , that do business in great waters ; \q1
These see the works of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and his wonders in the deep. \q1
For he commandeth , and raiseth the stormy wind , which lifteth up the waves thereof.\f + \fr 107.25 \ft raiseth: Heb. maketh to stand\f* \q1
They mount up to the heaven , they go down again to the depths : their soul is melted because of trouble. \q1
They reel to and fro , and stagger like a drunken man , and are at their wits’ end. \f + \fr 107.27 \ft are…: Heb. all their wisdom is swallowed up\f* \q1
Then they cry unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in their trouble , and he bringeth them out of their distresses. \q1
He maketh the storm a calm , so that the waves thereof are still. \q1
Then are they glad because they be quiet ; so he bringeth them unto their desired haven. \q1
Oh that \add men\add* would praise the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add for\add* his goodness , and \add for\add* his wonderful works to the children of men ! \q1
Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people , and praise him in the assembly of the elders. \b \q1
He turneth rivers into a wilderness , and the watersprings into dry ground ; \q1
A fruitful land into barrenness , for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.\f + \fr 107.34 \ft barrenness: Heb. saltiness\f* \q1
He turneth the wilderness into a standing water , and dry ground into watersprings. \q1
And there he maketh the hungry to dwell , that they may prepare a city for habitation ; \q1
And sow the fields , and plant vineyards , which may yield fruits of increase. \q1
He blesseth them also, so that they are multiplied greatly ; and suffereth not their cattle to decrease. \q1
Again, they are minished and brought low through oppression , affliction , and sorrow. \q1
He poureth contempt upon princes , and causeth them to wander in the wilderness , \add where there is\add* no way.\f + \fr 107.40 \ft wilderness: or, void place\f* \q1
Yet setteth he the poor on high from affliction , and maketh \add him\add* families like a flock.\f + \fr 107.41 \ft from: or, after\f* \q1
The righteous shall see \add it\add*, and rejoice : and all iniquity shall stop her mouth. \q1
Whoso \add is\add* wise , and will observe these \add things\add*, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
